{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ByQycRucFD9Hh6wuMLvTLQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Report\n\n### 1. Full File Contents\nThe file is complete and provided above (lines 1-676). It's a Close Call clock worker that handles precise minute-boundary price capture and round settlement.\n\n### 2. How Settlement Works\n\n**Settlement Function:** `settleRound()` (lines 326-583)\n\n**DB Transaction Pattern:**\n```typescript\nawait db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n  // All DB operations wrapped in a single atomic transaction\n  await txDb.insertCloseCallRound(...)\n  await txDb.settleCloseCallRound(...)\n  // ... profile lookups, transaction inserts, game entry upserts\n})\n```\n\nThe settlement persists atomically via `db.withTransaction()` which ensures all-or-nothing semantics. If any DB operation fails, the entire transaction rolls back, but **the on-chain settlement is already committed** (lines 569-572).\n\n### 3. Data Available at Settlement Time\n\nThe settlement function has access to:\n\n**From on-chain round account:**\n- `round.greenEntries` — array of green-side bets with player addresses and amounts\n- `round.redEntries` — array of red-side bets with player addresses and amounts\n- `round.openPrice` — BTC price at round creation\n- `round.openPriceExpo` — price exponent\n- `round.greenPool` — total green-side amount (lamports)\n- `round.redPool` — total red-side amount (lamports)\n\n**From external sources (fetched during settlement):**\n- `hermesPrice.price`, `hermesPrice.expo` — latest BTC close price from Pyth\n- `treasury`, `feeBps` — from PlatformConfig account\n\n**Computed during settlement:**\n- `totalPool` — greenPool + redPool\n- `computedFee` — `Math.floor(totalPool * feeBps / 10_000)`\n- `netPool` — totalPool - computedFee\n- `outcome` — determined by price comparison: \"refund\", \"green\", or \"red\"\n- `payoutLamports` — per-entry payout calculated based on their share of winning pool\n\n**From DB (profile lookups):**\n- `user_id` — for each participant who has a profile\n\n### 4. Where game.settled Event Should Be Emitted\n\n**There is no game.settled event emission in this file.**\n\nThe settlement function (lines 326-583) does NOT emit any event. It only:\n1. Builds and submits the on-chain settle transaction (line 408)\n2. Persists results to the database via atomic transaction (lines 440-568)\n3. Logs completion (lines 416-421)\n\nIf you need to emit a `game.settled` event, it should be emitted **after successful DB transaction completion** (after line 568, still within the try block), with access to:\n- `roundId` (line 437)\n- `pdaStr` (line 438)\n- `sig` (settlement tx signature, line 408)\n- `outcomeStr` (\"green\"|\"red\"|\"refund\", lines 410-414)\n- `greenEntries`, `redEntries`, `profileMap` (lines 425-427, 475-477)\n- All game entry data (lines 550-562)\n\nThe logical emission point would be just before the transaction block ends (around line 568), ensuring the database write succeeded."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eca57b8-16ed-4d78-a3fe-64a6180800ed","uuid":"0c10d3e6-f3af-4ec3-9085-d3acf5d80d08","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:01:39.010Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full contents of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` and report back:\n1. The full file contents\n2. How settlement works (what function, what DB transaction pattern)\n3. What data is available at settlement time (round info, players, fees, etc.)\n4. Where exactly the game.settled event should be emitted","agentId":"a0c34add15a2be9a4","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Report\n\n### 1. Full File Contents\nThe file is complete and provided above (lines 1-676). It's a Close Call clock worker that handles precise minute-boundary price capture and round settlement.\n\n### 2. How Settlement Works\n\n**Settlement Function:** `settleRound()` (lines 326-583