{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DuKqK91GsF5p6uEGeMga7o","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Here's a comprehensive report:\n\n## Pattern Analysis: `game.settled` Events in settle-tx.ts\n\n### 1. **Exact Event Emission Pattern**\n\nThere are two game types handled, with distinct `game` field values:\n\n**For Coinflip (line 442-466):**\n```\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {\n  roundId: round.match_id,\n  roundPda: pda,\n  game: \"coinflip\",\n  players: [...],\n  feeLamports: String(feeAmount),\n  settledAt,\n});\n```\n\n**For Lord (line 729-743):**\n```\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {\n  roundId: round.match_id,\n  roundPda: pda,\n  game: \"lord\",\n  players: [...],\n  feeLamports: String(feeAmount),\n  settledAt,\n});\n```\n\n### 2. **emitEvent() Call Signature and Payload Structure**\n\n```\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {\n  roundId: string,           // round.match_id\n  roundPda: string,          // pda (PublicKey converted to string)\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\", // game type identifier\n  players: Array<{...}>,     // see #3 below\n  feeLamports: string,       // String(feeAmount)\n  settledAt: string,         // ISO 8601 timestamp\n});\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- First param: `txDb.rawSql` (the raw SQL connection from within the transaction)\n- Second param: `EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED` (imported constant)\n- Third param: Payload object with exact field names\n- All amounts are stringified (feeLamports, amountLamports, payoutLamports)\n\n### 3. **Players Array Construction**\n\n**For Coinflip (two-player, line 446-462):**\n```typescript\nplayers: [\n  {\n    userId: creatorUserId ?? creator.toBase58(),\n    wallet: creator.toBase58(),\n    amountLamports: String(entryAmount),\n    isWinner: winner.equals(creator),\n    payoutLamports: winner.equals(creator) ? String(payoutAmount) : \"0\",\n    isCreator: true,\n  },\n  {\n    userId: opponentUserId ?? opponent.toBase58(),\n    wallet: opponent.toBase58(),\n    amountLamports: String(entryAmount),\n    isWinner: winner.equals(opponent),\n    payoutLamports: winner.equals(opponent) ? String(payoutAmount) : \"0\",\n    isCreator: false,\n  },\n]\n```\n\n**For Lord (multi-player, line 733-740):**\n```typescript\nplayers: [...playerAgg.entries()].map(([wallet, agg]) => ({\n  userId: profileMap.get(wallet)?.user_id ?? wallet,\n  wallet,\n  amountLamports: String(agg.total),\n  isWinner: agg.isWinner,\n  payoutLamports: agg.isWinner ? String(payoutAmount) : \"0\",\n  isCreator: serializedEntries[0]?.player === wallet, // first entry is creator\n}))\n```\n\n**Notable patterns:**\n- `userId`: Preferentially uses `user_id` from profile lookup; fallback to wallet address (toBase58())\n- `wallet`: Always PublicKey.toBase58()\n- `amountLamports`: Always stringified (String() wrapper)\n- `isWinner`: Boolean, determined by comparing wallet to winner\n- `payoutLamports`: String of payoutAmount if winner, \"0\" if loser\n- `isCreator`: For coinflip—explicit boolean; for lord—determined by checking if first entry's player equals wallet\n\n### 4. **How feeLamports is Obtained**\n\n**For Coinflip (line 276):**\n```typescript\nconst pool = entryAmount * 2n;\nconst feeAmount = Number((pool * BigInt(feeBps)) / 10_000n);\nconst payoutAmount = Number(pool) - feeAmount;\n```\n\n**For Lord (line 553):**\n```typescript\nconst feeAmount = Number((roundData.totalAmountLamports * BigInt(feeBps)) / 10_000n);\nconst payoutAmount = Number(roundData.totalAmountLamports) - feeAmount;\n```\n\n**Pattern:**\n- `feeBps` is a basis point value read from on-chain config (e.g., 500 = 5%)\n- Formula: `(totalAmount * feeBps) / 10_000` (where feeBps are basis points)\n- Result is a Number (not BigInt)\n- Stringified when emitting: `String(feeAmount)`\n\n### 5. **Event Emission Within DB Transaction**\n\nBoth patterns are **within a `db.withTransaction()` block**, which passes `txDb` (transaction-scoped DB connection):\n\n```typescript\nawait db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n  // Update phase\n  await txDb.updateRoundPhase(pda, \"settled\", {...});\n  \n  // Insert game entries\n  await txDb.insertGameEntries(...);\n  \n  // Insert operator event\n  await txDb.insertOperatorEvent(...);\n  \n  // Emit event USING txDb.rawSql\n  await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {\n    ...\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Key detail:** The `emitEvent()` call uses `txDb.rawSql` (not `db.rawSql`) to ensure the event is emitted atomically as part of the transaction. This guarantees the event will only be persisted if all other updates in the transaction succeed.\n\n---\n\n**File Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eca57b8-16ed-4d78-a3fe-64a6180800ed","uuid":"4dbc9f97-b431-42ea-bf92-bb789853cdfb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:02:01.770Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` and report back:\n1. The exact pattern used to emit `game.settled` events for coinflip and lord\n2. The exact `emitEvent()` call signature and payload construction\n3. How players[] array is built (with userId, wallet, amountLamports, isWinner, payoutLamports, isCreator)\n4. How feeLamports is obtained\n5. How the event is emitted within the DB transaction\n\nI need this to replicate the same pattern in closecall-clock.ts.","agentId":"aa42e1f4dd283f2b8","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Here's a comprehensive report:\n\n## Pattern Analysis: `game.settled` Events in settle-tx.ts\n\n### 1. **Exact Event Emission Pattern**\n\nThere are two game types handled, with distinct `game` field values:\n\n**For Coinflip (line 442-466):**\n```\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SET