{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012jf9LmiuJjw8ajAdHxfbKe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Integration Test Analysis Report\n\n### 1. **How the existing `game.settled` event test works (iteration 1 for coinflip)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` (lines 939-1054)\n\n**Test Flow**:\n1. **Setup**: Create JWT tokens and insert player profiles into `player_profiles` table for both creator and opponent so event payloads include user IDs\n2. **Create Round**: Call `POST /coinflip/create` API endpoint to create a match, returns `matchPda`, `matchId`, and `commitment`\n3. **Mock Join State**: Simulate on-chain join by:\n   - Building match account data with `PHASE_LOCKED` (phase = 1) using `buildMatchAccountData()`\n   - Setting the account in `MockConnection` with the coinflip program as owner\n   - Transitioning the DB round to \"locked\" state via `db.updateRoundPhase()`\n4. **Settle**: Call `settleMatch()` worker function directly with the match PDA\n5. **Verify Event**: Query `event_queue` table for `event_type = 'game.settled'`, verify:\n   - Exactly 1 event row exists with status = \"pending\"\n   - Payload contains: `roundId`, `roundPda`, `game: \"coinflip\"`, `feeLamports`, `settledAt`\n   - Players array has 2 entries with correct structure: `userId`, `wallet`, `amountLamports`, `isWinner`, `payoutLamports`, `isCreator`\n   - Exactly one winner (the other is a loser with payout = \"0\")\n   - Fee calculation is correct: `pool * feeBps / 10000` (example: 10M lamports * 500 bps / 10000 = 500K)\n\n**Event Emission Code** (`settle-tx.ts`, lines 438-466):\n```typescript\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {\n  roundId: round.match_id,\n  roundPda: pda,\n  game: \"coinflip\",\n  players: [...],\n  feeLamports: String(feeAmount),\n  settledAt,\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Test helpers/utilities available for creating test data**\n\n**Key Test Utilities in integration.test.ts**:\n\n| Utility | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `makeSql()` (lines 39-47) | Creates postgres connection from DATABASE_URL or Unix socket |\n| `makeJwt(wallet, userId)` (lines 59-67) | Generates HS256 JWT token with wallet, subject, and 1h expiry |\n| `userIdFromWallet(wallet)` (lines 69-71) | Derives user_id from wallet: `usr_${wallet.slice(0,8).toLowerCase()}` |\n| `buildMatchAccountData(params)` (lines 215-246) | Encodes coinflip match account data (creator, opponent, phase, commitment, etc.) |\n| `buildConfigAccountData(treasury)` (lines 248-255) | Encodes coinflip config account data |\n| `buildPlatformConfigData(treasury, feeBps)` (lines 261-271) | Builds PlatformConfig with 8-byte discriminator, authority, treasury, fee_bps |\n| `MockConnection` class (lines 82-209) | Minimal Solana Connection mock with in-memory account storage, supports filters, sendRawTransaction, confirmTransaction |\n\n**Mock Connection Methods**:\n- `setAccount(pubkey, data, opts)` — Store account in memory\n- `removeAccount(pubkey)` — Delete account\n- `getAccountInfo(pubkey)` — Retrieve account\n- `getProgramAccounts(programId, config)` — Filter accounts by program ID and optional filters (dataSize, memcmp)\n- `getLatestBlockhash()`, `getSlot()`, `getBalance()`, `confirmTransaction()` — Standard Solana methods\n\n---\n\n### 3. **How closecall rounds are represented in the DB**\n\n**Schema** (`migrations/004_closecall_rounds.sql`):\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE closecall_rounds (\n  round_id        TEXT         PRIMARY KEY,\n  pda             TEXT         UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n  server_key      TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  phase           TEXT         DEFAULT 'open' CHECK (phase IN ('open', 'settled', 'refunded')),\n  open_price      BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  open_price_expo INT          NOT NULL,\n  close_price     BIGINT,                        -- NULL until settled\n  outcome         TEXT         DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (outcome IN ('pending', 'green', 'red', 'refund')),\n  green_pool      BIGINT       DEFAULT 0,\n  red_pool        BIGINT       DEFAULT 0,\n  total_fee       BIGINT       DEFAULT 0,\n  settle_tx       TEXT,                          -- Transaction signature\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at      TIMESTAMPTZ                    -- NULL until settled\n);\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_closecall_rounds_phase` — Query by phase\n- `idx_closecall_rounds_settled_at` — Query by settlement time (descending)\n- `idx_cc_rounds_settled` — Settled rounds only\n\n**Key Fields**:\n- `round_id`: Minute boundary timestamp (primary key)\n- `phase`: Oracle-resolved lifecycle (open → settled or refunded)\n- `outcome`: Resolution (pending, green, red, refund) — resolved via Pyth price\n- `open_price` / `close_price`: BTC prices with expo for decimals\n- `green_pool` / `red_pool`: Pari-mutuel pools (lamports)\n- `settle_tx`: On-chain settlement transaction signature\n\n**Game Entries for Closecall** (`migrations/007_game_entries.sql`):\n- Stored in same `game_entries` table as coinflip/lord\n- `game = 'closecall'`, `side IN ('green', 'red')`, `round_pda` references closecall round\n- Written at bet time, updated at settlement via UPSERT\n- Refunded entries: `is_winner = NULL`, `payout_lamports = amount_lamports`\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Test database setup/teardown pattern**\n\n**BeforeAll** (lines 295-385):\n1. Create postgres connection via `makeSql()` (uses DATABASE_URL or Unix socket)\n2. Drop and recreate referral tables (integration test creates these manually)\n3. Create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables\n4. Initialize `db = createDb(DATABASE_URL, rawSql)` — loads migrations (rounds, closecall_rounds, game_entries, event_queue, etc.)\n\n**BeforeEach** (lines 392-441):\n1. **Table Cleanup**: `TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events, event_queue, game_entries, transactions, player_profiles, referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`\n2. **Reset PlatformConfig cache** — ensures each test reads from its own mock\n3. **Fresh MockConnection** — clear accounts\n4. **Pre-populate mock accounts**:\n   - Entropy account (32 bytes with test data)\n   - CoinflipConfig PDA (derived from \"coinflip_config\")\n   - PlatformConfig PDA (with fee_bps = 500 = 5%)\n5. **Rebuild Hono app** — fresh routes with current mock connection\n\n**AfterAll** (lines 387-390):\n1. `await db.close()` — close postgres pool\n2. `await rawSql.end()` — terminate raw connection\n\n**Pattern**: Full isolation per test via TRUNCATE + RESTART IDENTITY, cached mock state reset, fresh app instance\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Closecall-specific test files**\n\n**Devnet E2E Test** (`e2e/devnet/closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts`):\n- Full player lifecycle: bet GREEN/RED → wait for settlement → verify outcome\n- Tests actual on-chain Solana transactions (not mocked)\n- Includes helper types and API client functions:\n  - `BackendCloseCallRound` interface (roundId, pda, phase, openPrice, closePrice, outcome, pools, entries, etc.)\n  - `fetchCurrentRound()` — GET `/closecall/current-round`\n  - `fetchHistory(limit)` — GET `/closecall/history?limit=N`\n  - `placeBetViaApi()` — POST `/closecall/bet` + sign + submit\n  - `waitForSettlement()` — Poll until settled/refunded (120s timeout)\n\n**No dedicated unit test file for closecall found** — only devnet E2E test exists. Integration tests focus on coinflip; closecall testing is end-to-end against real devnet.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Event Types Available**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",              // ← For all games (coinflip, lord, closecall)\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n```\n\nThe `GAME_SETTLED` event is generic and used for all game types (coinflip, lord, closecall) — the payload includes `game: string` to differentiate."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eca57b8-16ed-4d78-a3fe-64a6180800ed","uuid":"462266fd-dbb1-407a-afcb-6e6a8b82164d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:02:58.654Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` and report:\n1. How the existing `game.settled` event test works (the one added in iteration 1 for coinflip)\n2. What test helpers/utilities are available for creating test data\n3. How closecall rounds are represented in the DB (check the closecall-related tables, schemas, or any existing closecall tests)\n4. The test database setup/teardown pattern\n5. Also check if there are any closecall-specific test files\n\nAlso read the event-types.ts file to see the current event types.","agentId":"a047babb6de14d453","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Integration Test Analysis Report\n\n### 1. **How the existing `game.settled` event test works (iteration 1 for coinflip)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` (lines 939-1054)\n\n**Test Flow**:\n1. **Setup**: Create JWT tokens and insert player profiles into `player_profiles` table for both creator and opponent so event payloads include user IDs\n2. **Create Round**: Call `POST /coinflip/create` API endpoint to create a match, returns `matchPda`, `matchId`, and `commitment`\n3. **Mock Join State**: Simulate on-chain join by:\n   - Building matc