{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017sWZHEt75rtcKF3tGqjVJe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Analysis: Close Call Round Account Data & Test Setup\n\n### 1. Decoder Functions (account-decoder.ts)\n\n**`closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter()` — Line 293-297:**\n\n```typescript\nexport function closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter(): {\n  memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string };\n} {\n  return { memcmp: closecallCoder.memcmp(\"CloseCallRound\") };\n}\n```\n\nThis returns a memcmp filter object with an 8-byte discriminator offset at position 0, using Anchor's `memcmp()` which internally encodes the discriminator in base58 format. The discriminator bytes are `[205, 51, 62, 226, 33, 11, 235, 40]` (from IDL line 550-559).\n\n**`decodeCloseCallRound()` — Line 239-259:**\n\n```typescript\nexport function decodeCloseCallRound(data: Buffer): DecodedCloseCallRound {\n  const raw: any = closecallCoder.decode(\"CloseCallRound\", data);\n  return {\n    minuteTs: bnToBigInt(raw.minute_ts),\n    server: raw.server,\n    phase: closeCallPhaseToNumber(raw.phase),\n    greenEntries: decodeBetEntries(raw.green_entries),\n    redEntries: decodeBetEntries(raw.red_entries),\n    greenPool: bnToBigInt(raw.green_pool),\n    redPool: bnToBigInt(raw.red_pool),\n    openPrice: bnToBigInt(raw.open_price),\n    openPriceExpo: raw.open_price_expo,\n    closePrice: bnToBigInt(raw.close_price),\n    createdAt: bnToBigInt(raw.created_at),\n    bettingEndsAt: bnToBigInt(raw.betting_ends_at),\n    resolveDeadline: bnToBigInt(raw.resolve_deadline),\n    outcome: outcomeToNumber(raw.outcome),\n    totalFee: bnToBigInt(raw.total_fee),\n    bump: raw.bump,\n  };\n}\n```\n\nHelper function at line 230-237:\n```typescript\nfunction decodeBetEntries(\n  entries: any[],\n): Array<{ player: PublicKey; amountLamports: bigint }> {\n  return entries.map((e: any) => ({\n    player: e.player,\n    amountLamports: bnToBigInt(e.amount_lamports),\n  }));\n}\n```\n\n### 2. DecodedCloseCallRound Interface (Lines 125-142)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface DecodedCloseCallRound {\n  minuteTs: bigint;\n  server: PublicKey;\n  phase: number;\n  greenEntries: Array<{ player: PublicKey; amountLamports: bigint }>;\n  redEntries: Array<{ player: PublicKey; amountLamports: bigint }>;\n  greenPool: bigint;\n  redPool: bigint;\n  openPrice: bigint;\n  openPriceExpo: number;\n  closePrice: bigint;\n  createdAt: bigint;\n  bettingEndsAt: bigint;\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;\n  outcome: number;\n  totalFee: bigint;\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Phase enum mapping:**\n- `Open = 0`\n- `Settled = 1`\n- `Refunded = 2`\n\n**Outcome enum mapping:**\n- `Pending = 0`\n- `Green = 1`\n- `Red = 2`\n- `Refund = 3`\n\n### 3. On-Chain CloseCallRound Struct Layout (Rust @ state.rs, lines 58-102)\n\n```rust\n#[account]\n#[derive(InitSpace)]\npub struct CloseCallRound {\n    pub minute_ts: i64,           // 8 bytes\n    pub server: Pubkey,            // 32 bytes\n    pub phase: CloseCallPhase,     // 1 byte (enum)\n    \n    #[max_len(32)]\n    pub green_entries: Vec<BetEntry>,  // Vec header (4 bytes len) + N * BetEntry (40 bytes each)\n    #[max_len(32)]\n    pub red_entries: Vec<BetEntry>,    // Vec header (4 bytes len) + N * BetEntry (40 bytes each)\n    \n    pub green_pool: u64,           // 8 bytes\n    pub red_pool: u64,             // 8 bytes\n    \n    pub open_price: i64,           // 8 bytes\n    pub open_price_expo: i32,      // 4 bytes\n    pub close_price: i64,          // 8 bytes\n    \n    pub created_at: i64,           // 8 bytes\n    pub betting_ends_at: i64,      // 8 bytes\n    pub resolve_deadline: i64,     // 8 bytes\n    \n    pub outcome: Outcome,          // 1 byte (enum)\n    pub total_fee: u64,            // 8 bytes\n    pub bump: u8,                  // 1 byte\n}\n\npub struct BetEntry {\n    pub player: Pubkey,            // 32 bytes\n    pub amount_lamports: u64,      // 8 bytes\n}\n```\n\n**Critical serialization notes:**\n- 8-byte Anchor discriminator prepended (bytes 0-7): `[205, 51, 62, 226, 33, 11, 235, 40]`\n- Vec<BetEntry> uses Borsh encoding: 4-byte length (LE u32) + packed entries\n- Maximum account size: 8 (discriminator) + 8 + 32 + 1 + (4 + 32*40) + (4 + 32*40) + 8 + 8 + 8 + 4 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 1 + 8 + 1 = ~2704 bytes\n\n### 4. MockConnection Class Features (integration.test.ts, lines 82-209)\n\n**Constructor & properties:**\n```typescript\nclass MockConnection {\n  private _slot = 200;\n  private _accounts = new Map<string, { data: Buffer; lamports: number; owner: PublicKey; executable: boolean }>();\n  lastRawTx: Buffer | null = null;\n}\n```\n\n**`setAccount(pubkey, data, opts?)` — Line 102-113:**\n- Accepts PublicKey, Buffer data, optional lamports & owner\n- Stores in base58-encoded key map\n- Default: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL lamports, SystemProgram.programId owner\n- Tracks executable flag (defaults to false)\n\n**`getProgramAccounts(programId, config?)` — Lines 136-190:**\n- Supports filters: `{ dataSize: number }` and `{ memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string } }`\n- Decodes filter bytes from base58\n- Compares memcmp at specified offset using Buffer.subarray()\n- Returns matched accounts with rentEpoch set to 0\n- **Fully implements discriminator filtering needed for Close Call**\n\n**Other methods:**\n- `getAccountInfo(pubkey)` — returns account with rentEpoch\n- `getSlot()` — returns current slot (mutable)\n- `getLatestBlockhash()` — fixed fake blockhash\n- `getBalance()` — returns 2 SOL\n- `sendRawTransaction()` — stores and returns deterministic signature\n- `confirmTransaction()` — returns slot\n- `getBlockTime()` — returns current Unix timestamp\n\n### 5. Platform Config Reader (platform-config.ts)\n\n**PlatformConfig account layout (lines 28-32):**\n```\noffset  0..8   discriminator (8 bytes)\noffset  8..40  authority (Pubkey, 32 bytes)\noffset 40..72  treasury (Pubkey, 32 bytes)\noffset 72..74  fee_bps (u16 LE)\n```\n\n**`getPlatformConfig(connection)` — Lines 63-69:**\n- Cached accessor that reads from chain on first call\n- Uses `fetchPlatformConfig()` internally\n- Returns `{ feeBps: number; treasury: PublicKey }`\n- **Same function used by coinflip test** (line 416-421 of integration.test.ts)\n\n**Close Call reading pattern:** Close Call settlement reads platform config via the same `getPlatformConfig()` call to get fee_bps and treasury. No dedicated getter needed.\n\n### 6. HermesFetcher Interface & createHermesFetcher (pyth-poster.ts, lines 29-75)\n\n**Interface definition (lines 29-31):**\n```typescript\nexport interface HermesFetcher {\n  fetchLatestBtcPrice(): Promise<HermesPrice | null>;\n}\n```\n\n**Return type HermesPrice (lines 21-27):**\n```typescript\nexport interface HermesPrice {\n  price: bigint;           // Raw Pyth price (e.g., 69500 for $69,500)\n  expo: number;            // Exponent (e.g., -2 means divide by 100)\n  publishTime: number;     // Pyth publish Unix timestamp\n  priceHuman: number;      // Computed: price * 10^expo (human readable)\n  vaaBase64: string | null; // Base64-encoded VAA for price proof\n}\n```\n\n**`createHermesFetcher(endpoint?)` — Lines 37-75:**\n- Takes optional endpoint (default: \"https://hermes.pyth.network\")\n- Returns object implementing HermesFetcher interface\n- Uses HermesClient from @pythnetwork/hermes-client\n- Calls `getLatestPriceUpdates([BTC_USD_FEED_ID], { encoding: \"base64\", parsed: true })`\n- Extracts: price (bigint), expo (number), publishTime (number)\n- Extracts VAA from binary data (base64)\n- Returns null on network error with logging\n- BTC_USD_FEED_ID: `\"0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43\"`\n\n---\n\n## Building Mock Close Call Round Account Data for Tests\n\nTo create mock Close Call round account data for testing, you would:\n\n1. **Create encoder function** (add to account-decoder.ts):\n   ```typescript\n   export async function encodeCloseCallRound(\n     fields: DecodedCloseCallRound,\n   ): Promise<Buffer> {\n     return closecallCoder.encode(\"CloseCallRound\", {\n       minute_ts: new BN(fields.minuteTs.toString()),\n       server: fields.server,\n       phase: /* convert number back to enum variant */,\n       green_entries: fields.greenEntries.map(e => ({\n         player: e.player,\n         amount_lamports: new BN(e.amountLamports.toString()),\n       })),\n       red_entries: fields.redEntries.map(e => ({\n         player: e.player,\n         amount_lamports: new BN(e.amountLamports.toString()),\n       })),\n       green_pool: new BN(fields.greenPool.toString()),\n       red_pool: new BN(fields.redPool.toString()),\n       open_price: new BN(fields.openPrice.toString()),\n       open_price_expo: fields.openPriceExpo,\n       close_price: new BN(fields.closePrice.toString()),\n       created_at: new BN(fields.createdAt.toString()),\n       betting_ends_at: new BN(fields.bettingEndsAt.toString()),\n       resolve_deadline: new BN(fields.resolveDeadline.toString()),\n       outcome: /* convert number back to enum variant */,\n       total_fee: new BN(fields.totalFee.toString()),\n       bump: fields.bump,\n     });\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Use MockConnection.setAccount()** with discriminator filter:\n   ```typescript\n   const roundData = await encodeCloseCallRound({...});\n   mockConn.setAccount(roundPda, roundData, { owner: CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID });\n   ```\n\n3. **Filter via getProgramAccounts():**\n   ```typescript\n   const accounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(\n     CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID,\n     { filters: [closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter()] }\n   );\n   ```\n\nThe MockConnection handles base58 decoding of the discriminator filter automatically, making it a drop-in replacement for the real Solana Connection."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eca57b8-16ed-4d78-a3fe-64a6180800ed","uuid":"41a1413e-f58d-4208-9b0d-78116b44d550","timestamp":