f this is a long-running test, pass a timeout value as the last argument or configure it globally with \"testTimeout\".\n\n⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯ Failed Tests 1 ⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯\n\n FAIL  services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts > Integration: create → join → settle lifecycle > closecall settlement emits game.settled event with correct payload shape\nError: Test timed out in 5000ms.\nIf this is a long-running test, pass a timeout value as the last argument or configure it globally with \"testTimeout\".\n⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯[1/1]⎯\n\n Test Files  1 failed (1)\n      Tests  1 failed | 8 passed (9)\n   Start at  19:14:17\n   Duration  14.33s (transform 1.28s, setup 0ms, collect 2.98s, tests 7.18s, environment 0ms, prepare 560ms)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false,"dangerouslyDisableSandbox":true}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Coj2iKJUst5AeSgkpoCGgQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test is timing out because `captureBoundaryPrice()` is trying to match the Hermes publish time against the *current* minute boundary. The current boundary is `1775243640` but my mock hermes returns `publishTime: Number(minuteTs) + 60` which is a past timestamp (2 minutes ago).\n\nThe issue: `tick()` computes `boundaryTs = Math.floor(Date.now() / 60_000) * 60` which is the CURRENT minute boundary. Then `captureBoundaryPrice(boundaryTs)` polls hermes until `result.publishTime >= boundaryTs`. \n\nMy mock returns a fixed publishTime that's 2 minutes in the past, so it never satisfies the condition and times out after 10 retries. I need to make the mock dynamic so it returns the current timestamp instead of a stale one.\n\nUpdating the mock hermes...\n\nNow I see the real issue: even with the publishTime fixed, `settleRound()` will use the mock's close price of 69600 (which is higher than the open price of 69500), so the outcome should be \"green\". The candleCloseTime check will also pass since it's based on a timestamp from 2 minutes ago. I need to adjust the test setup to handle this correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5942,"cache_read_input_tokens":101061,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5942},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eca57b8-16ed-4d78-a3fe-64a6180800ed","uuid":"dc318cd8-9a53-4b4d-8ad4-f32df115afe2"}
